post_text:
Prior to the Governor's fall sports order, we were all just hoping the Governor would let our kids play. We are lucky right now to have a season at all for our Fall athletes.

After yesterday's late release of the Governor's order for Fall sports, we are still working with our athletic league on the details of spectators at athletic events. The order is extremely restrictive. These events will clearly be primarily parent only events to comply with the order. It is also likely that the numbers of people permitted to attend will be different at each school we travel to. It is likely that every "away" game will have a smaller number of spectators allowed than our home games.

post_text:
Based on Governor Dewine‚Äôs mandate on August 4, 2020 that all K-12 students must wear masks to school, coupled with Lake Elementary School‚Äôs lack of air conditioning, the start date of the Lake Local School District will be pushed back to TUESDAY, SEPTEMBER 8, 2020.

While we look forward to seeing our students as quickly as possible, we think it is in the best interests of approximately 600 of our youngest Flyers and the 85 staff members in the elementary school to wait the extra time so, hopefully, the weather will cool down and the building will be more comfortable.

Thank you to the people who offered last night to buy additional window air conditioners to install in Lake Elementary classrooms. Unfortunately, there is not enough electric capacity in that building to handle the additional load, but your generosity is much appreciated.

Additional information will be forthcoming from each building in the next several days. Once again, we appreciate your patience and flexibility as we work through this crisis.

Dear Parents,

Our 2019-2020 middle school yearbooks were published and distributed with 50+ spelling errors. We have been working very closely with Jostens to get these errors corrected and we have had the middle school yearbooks reprinted with the necessary corrections. We are asking that parents return the yearbook with errors in exchange for a corrected one.

Please bring your student's yearbook to the middle school office starting on Monday, August 3, 2020 from 8:00 am until 2:00 pm to exchange it for a corrected one.

If you have any questions or concerns, please contact Jodi Takats at jtakats@lakeschools.org.

Thank you!

In the next ten days we will have an outline ready for the public. There are still details to work out but there will be two options for kids this fall. The first option is to have students attend classes on campus. We intend to implement as many of the guidelines suggested by the Ohio Department of Education as we can in a practical manner. June 4, 2020

Dear Lake Community:

Earlier this week Governor Dewine announced that his goal is to have Ohio schools open this fall. He also stated that there would be broad guidelines for schools to follow and school districts will have control over how the day looks within those guidelines. What the governor did not disclose was when those guidelines will be released and how strict they will be. Until districts are notified of those parameters, we cannot proceed with plans on how to educate our students for the 2020-21 school year.In the next few weeks we will be releasing the results of the recent survey we asked you to complete. Like the other districts, who put out a similar survey, we‚Ä¶ More

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians

In spite of the continuing uncertainty of what next year‚Äôs school year will look like, our administrative team has been looking at different scenarios based on tentative guidelines sent to us by Governor Dewine‚Äôs office and the Ohio Department of Education. As we continue to study our options, a short survey will be sent out sometime in the next several days asking for your opinions. Please help us by completing the survey.

On a different topic, the Class of 2020 will be coming to campus this Saturday to take part in a graduation ceremony that will be released via video on May 31. More details will be released soon on a parade that will be held featuring this outstanding bunch of graduates.

Jim Witt

Superintendent

May 5, 2020

Dear Lake Community --

A few items to bring to your attention:

You are all invited to the parade we will be holding on campus on Wednesday, May 6 at 6:30 p.m. to honor our entire staff. We encourage you to wear Flyer colors, make signs, honk your horns, and wave to our employees as you follow the route that has been mapped out. Please do NOT stop for any reason, do NOT bring gifts for anyone, and respect the social distancing requirements. We want this event to go smoothly and to be a great time for everyone!

This week is Teacher Appreciation Week. I told our teachers yesterday that they have never been more appreciated than during this crazy time. Please join me in applauding‚Ä¶

post_text:
Update from the superintendent:

Good afternoon --

Earlier this afternoon, Governor Dewine announced that schools will remain closed for the rest of the school year. In anticipation of that information, we had already scheduled a tentative administrative team meeting to discuss our priorities going forward for early next week. As those plans begin to take shape later this week and early next week, they will be shared with you as quickly as possible. Until then, please be patient with us as there are many subjects to tackle.

In the next few days there may be a reluctance on the part of students to complete work because of this decision by the governor. Please be encouraging and understanding. This is different for everyone and difficult for most.

Hang in there. We will get through this together

In the next few days there may be a reluctance on the part of students to complete work because of this decision by the governor. Please be encouraging and understanding. This is different for everyone and difficult for most.

Hang in there. We will get through this together

Families interested in their child, aged 3-5 years, attending Lake Preschool in the fall, may fill out an electronic form on Lake Preschool's website http://www.lakeschools.org/schools/lake-preschool/. The link to the electronic form will be posted on Monday, April 6th at 11 am. Pre-registration is on a first come first serve basis. Families who register for Lake Preschool will be contacted via mail no later than June 1, 2020.

post_text:
A message from the Superintendent:
Good morning --

Thank you parents for your help in delivering lessons. Your help in your child's schoolwork is an integral part of this new normal. A couple of items to bring to your attention:

- April 6 through May 1 are now virtual school days.
- April 10 and April 13 are days off because that is how they were scheduled on our original calendar.
- Food will continue to be available on Wednesdays from 10:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m.
- If you get a chance, please send us your pictures of your students working on school work or doing something fun.

Our staff misses the kids!

Thank you for your continued help and support. Have a great weekend.

Lake Junior, Aeden Alder, will be attending the American Legion Buckeye Boys State held June 14-21 at Miami University! Thank you to the Wood County Council of the American Legion who is sponsoring Aiden through the Pemberville Freedom Post 183. Click here to find out more about Buckeye Boys State: https://www.ohiobuckeyeboysstate.com/

Buckeye Girls State is held on the campus of the University of Mount Union, Alliance, Ohio. The 2020 program begins on Sunday, June 14th and ends on Saturday, June 20th. Lake Junior, Natalia Castellucio was chosen to represent Lake at Buckeye Girls State. Delal Abbas and Logan Fais were chosen to be alternates. All three girls were selected and are sponsored
by the Troy-Webster American Legion Auxiliary Unit 240 in Luckey,
Ohio. Thank you!!! Click here to find out more about Buckeye Girls State: http://buckeyegirlsstate.org/

While there are no confirmed cases in this area of the coronavirus (COVID-19), we wanted to share how we are monitoring the situation and what precautions we can all take during this flu season. Lake Schools‚Ä¶

post_text:
Lake Parents & Community --

On Wednesday, March 11 from 6:30-8:00 pm Detective Sgt. Amy Gloor from the Ottawa County Sheriff's office will be presenting, "Parenting in Today's Digital World" for parents, guardians, and community members. This presentation is for adults only. Sgt. Gloor will discuss the dangers of social media and other cell phone and device usage that are ever present in our students' lives.

During the school day on March 11, our 4th grade through 12th grade students will be spending time listening to Sgt. Gloor speak on the same subjects.

I encourage you to join us on March 11 at 6:30 in the Lake High School Auditorium to learn more about this important topic.

Jim Witt, Superintendent

post_text: The 7th and 8th grade quiz bowl team was back at the buzzers last night. This was a match to remember! The Flyers won round 1 with a score of 30 to 0. In round two, the team scored 44 more points, bringing the score to Lake 74, Woodmore 12. In the final round, the points just kept coming in with a score of Lake 50, Woodmore 6 - bringing the final score to Lake 124, Woodmore 18. This match was awesome because each and every team member scored points! Derk Jackson brought in 4 points, Joah Herman 8 points, James Shank and Zeke Balsmeyer each brought in 12, Jon Spect brought in 16, McKenna Miller brought in 22, and 8th grader Dylan Keel scored an astounding 50 points. Mrs. Janes is so proud of this quiz bowl team and all their hard work! The Flyers will be at BG Christian tonight and Eastwood on Monday. The team is 4 and 1. Go Flyers! ‚úàÔ∏è #flyerpride

shared_text:
State Representative Haraz N. Ghanbari is at Lake High School (Millbury, Ohio).
February 1 at 3:00 AM ¬∑ Millbury, OH ¬∑

Thank you to the families of Lake High School (Millbury, Ohio) and the Otsego Local School District for welcoming military veterans to watch your boy‚Äôs basketball teams compete, Friday, Jan. 31, 2020. The VFW 9963 Walbridge Oh presented the colors this evening as veterans joined them on court for the National Anthem beautifully sung by Lisa Feather.

A hearty congratulations to Lake Local Schools Elementary Principal Mandy Wilburn who received the 2019 VFW Walbridge Post 9963 Educator of The Year Crystal Apple Award for her tireless efforts in spearheading the designing and implementing the Veterans Wall located at Lake High School. The award was presented by Post 9963 members Ken Gilsdorf and Kent Greenlese this evening.

January 19 at 9:51 PM ¬∑

Great job to our MS and HS teams today! They both brought home 2nd place finishes!! ‚Ä¢‚Ä¢ Today was our final competition of the season for the MS team. They have worked so hard this season and have overcome so many obstacles throughout the year. Thank you for your hard work - we are so proud of you! Our HS team rocked it today and HIT, keeping all stunts in the air and brought the energy and spirit. Having a stranger say, ‚Äúyour girls were so much fun to watch,‚Äù is an amazing feeling! It was their best performance of the year!! We‚Äôre disappointed with the scores we received, but our confidence and strength for the Regional competition is so high! Way to go, Flyers! ‚úàÔ∏èüíô

post_text: Our 6th graders are headed back to Camp Michindoh in February! If you would be willing to help offset the cost for a student who might not be able to make the financial commitment, please contact Katie Beard, Middle School Principal at 419-661-6523 or kbeard@lakeschools.org. Funds are due no later than January 31.

post_text: Meet Mrs. Woodbridge, second grade Title 1 teacher. Mrs. Woodbridge has taught at Lake Elementary for 10 years. Fun Fact: if she could eliminate one thing from her daily routine it would be making dinner!! I mean, she still wants to eat it - she just wants someone else to plan it and make it! Any takers?? #flyerpride #flyerfamily #staffshoutout ‚úàÔ∏è
